<subSubSection pageId="35" pageNumber="36" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1437,854,989]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,295,890,916]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Biology.</emphasis>
Associated with gall midge (
<taxonomicName box="[623,713,890,916]" class="Insecta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Diptera</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName box="[724,895,890,916]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Cecidomyiidae</taxonomicName>
) galls on undetermined trees (
<bibRefCitation author="Wang, Y. &amp; Chen, X. &amp; Pujade-Villar, J. &amp; Wu, H. &amp; He, J." box="[1234,1429,890,917]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="1034 - 1039" refId="ref55032" refString="Wang, Y., Chen, X., Pujade-Villar, J., Wu, H. &amp; He, J. (2010) The genus Saphonecrus Dalla-Torre &amp; Kieffer, 1910 (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae) in China, with descriptions of two new species. Biologia, 65, 1034 - 1039. https: // doi. org / 10.2478 / s 11756 - 010 - 0120 - 9" type="journal article" year="2010">
Wang 
<emphasis box="[1307,1357,890,916]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">et al</emphasis>
. 2010
</bibRefCitation>
) and hedgehog-like galls on leaf veins of 
<taxonomicName box="[624,739,926,953]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ciliaris">
<emphasis box="[624,739,926,953]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Q. ciliaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(sect. 
<taxonomicName box="[818,1005,926,952]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Cyclobalanopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[818,1005,926,952]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Cyclobalanopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Lobato-Vila, I. &amp; Wang, Y. &amp; Melika, G. &amp; Guo, R. &amp; Xiaoxue, J. &amp; Pujade-Villar, J." box="[1031,1321,926,953]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="1 - 28" refId="ref46786" refString="Lobato-Vila, I., Wang, Y., Melika, G., Guo, R., Xiaoxue, J. &amp; Pujade-Villar, J. (2021 b) A taxonomic review of the gall wasp genus Saphonecrus Dalla-Torre &amp; Kieffer and other oak cynipid inquilines (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae) from mainland China, with updated keys to Eastern Palaearctic and Oriental species. Zoological Studies, 60 (10), 1 - 28. https: // doi. org / 10.6620 / ZS. 2021.60 - 10" type="journal article" year="2021">
Lobato-Vila 
<emphasis box="[1178,1230,926,952]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">et al</emphasis>
. 2021b
</bibRefCitation>
). The gall inducers have yet to be confirmed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
